	• Docker run = pulls image and starts container 
	
		○ Docker run -d 
		○ -d = detached mode 
	• 
		○ Docker run -p6000:6379 (id / image name)
		○ -p = port binding between Host and Container Ports
		○ -p6000:6379 = 6000 is Host port number || 6379 is Container port number

	• Docker stop (id) = stops  the container
	• Docker start (id) = starts stopped container

	• Docker pull = to download a image for the Docker Hub

	• Docker ps = list running containers
		○ Docker ps -a 
		○ -a = lists running and stoppped container (History)
	
	• Docker images = shows all the images in my computer

	• Docker run -d -p6001:6379 --name redis-older redis:4.0
--name redis-older = naming a container
